{"lemma":"وَعْدَيْ","slug":"وَعْدَيْ","root":"#.ع.د","root_slug":"_-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَعْد","root":"وعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":49},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42110","n42114"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to promise (construed doubly transitive or someone بِ (bi) something)","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"هَلْ تَعِدُنِي بِذٰلِكَ؟","english":"Will you promise me (are you promising me) this?"},{"text":"بِطَرِيقَة أُخْرَى، أَعِدِ الكَرَّة، حَاوِلْ مَرَّة أُخْرَى","english":"In other words, try again"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to threaten with","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"هٰذِهِ جَهَنَّمُ ٱلَّتِي كُنْتُمْ تُوعَدُونَ","english":"This is the Hell with which you were threatened"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of وَعَدَ (waʕada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"promise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"threat, menace"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything promised or threatened"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/wa.ʕa.da/","/waʕd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42110","headword_ar":"وَعَدَ","root":"wEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEidu","text_ar":"يَعِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEodN","text_ar":"وَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidapN","text_ar":"عِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,) [in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the elided"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":",] or the latter is a quasi-inf. n., (L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEidN","text_ar":"مَوْعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEidapN","text_ar":"مَوْعِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb, K,) or the last is a quasi-inf. n., (L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEuwdN","text_ar":"مَوْعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEuwdapN","text_ar":"مَوْعُودَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) the last two being instances of inf. ns. of the measures"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEwulapN","text_ar":"مَفْعوُلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is trans. immediately, and by means of the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, Msb, K;) but some say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundant in this case; and most of the lexicologists disallow it with this form of the verb, allowing it only with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoEada","text_ar":"اَوْعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is also used with reference to good and evil: (S, L, Msb, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEadahu xayorFA","text_ar":"وَعَدَهُ خَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised him good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEadahu $ar~FA","text_ar":"وَعَدَهُ شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threatened him with evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Fr, Fs, S, L, Msb, K, &c.:) and, [accord. to some,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wEdh bixayorK","text_ar":"وعده بِخَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$ar~","text_ar":"بِشَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKoot, Msb.) When neither good nor evil is mentioned, if you mean the former, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEada","text_ar":"وَعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and if you mean the latter, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoEada","text_ar":"اَوْعَدَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S, L, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyEaAdN","text_ar":"اـِيعَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEiydN","text_ar":"وَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn., (S, L, Msb, K,) being one irregular inf. n., [or quasiinf. n.,] (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threatened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threatened with, evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoEadahu","text_ar":"اَوْعَدَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threatened him, menaced him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threatened him with evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twE~dhu","text_ar":"توعّدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaE~udN","text_ar":"تَوَعُّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"At~Edhu","text_ar":"اتّعدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) You also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorFA","text_ar":"خَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwEd","text_ar":"اوعد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (IAar, T, ISd, Msb, K;) but this is extr.: (L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$ar~K","text_ar":"بِشَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwEd","text_ar":"اوعد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threatened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"threatened with, evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, L, Msb, K:) when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is introduced after this form of the verb, it relates only to evil: (Fs, Msb:) but you also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~FA","text_ar":"شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwEdh","text_ar":"اوعده","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Failure of performance, with respect to a promise, the Arabs regard as a lie; but with regard to a threat, as generosity. A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA_in~iY waA_ino A^awoEadotuhu A^awo waEadotuhu\n                      \n                     \n                        lamuxolifu A_iyEaAdiY wamunojizu mawoEidiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily I, if I threaten him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promise him, fail to perform my threat, but fulfil my promise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) Nay, they do not apply the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xulofN","text_ar":"خُلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the failure of performing a threat. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomunaA yaEidu barodFA","text_ar":"يَوْمُنَا يَعِدُ بَرْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our day promises cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEadati AlA^arD","text_ar":"وَعَدَتِ الاَرض"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land promised good produce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAEadahu fawaEadahu","text_ar":"وَاعَدَهُ فَوَعَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3."}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K","Fr","T","Fs"]},{"entry_id":"n42114","headword_ar":"وَعْدٌ","root":"wEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidapN","text_ar":"عِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in which latter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the [elided]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEidN","text_ar":"مَوْعِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEidapN","text_ar":"مَوْعِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEuwdN","text_ar":"مَوْعُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoEuwdapN","text_ar":"مَوْعُودَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) see 1:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A promising; a promise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L;) meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of something good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, &c.:) pl. of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuEuwdN","text_ar":"وُعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IJ, L;) or this has no pl.: (T, S, L, Msb:) and of the second,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidaAtN","text_ar":"عِدَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, L, Msb:) (and of the ↓ third,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAEidu","text_ar":"مَوَاعِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mwEwd","text_ar":"موعود","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAEiydu","text_ar":"مَوَاعِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eidap","text_ar":"عِدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a prefixed n., [in a case of wasl,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is elided, (Fr, S, L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for it: (Fr, L:) a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^axolafuwka EidaY A@loA^amori A@l~a*iY waEaduwA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they have broken to thee the promise of the thing which they promised"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, S, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTiy~apN","text_ar":"عَطِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEidapu","text_ar":"العِدَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A promise is"},{"kind":"text","text":"equivalent to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gift"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., it is base to break it as it is to take back a gift. A proverb. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alvry~aA","text_ar":"الثريَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEadahu Eidapa","text_ar":"وَعَدَهُ عِدَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlqamari","text_ar":"بِالقَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He promised him as the moon promises the Pleiades"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for the moon and the Pleiades are in conjunction once in every month. Another proverb. (TA.) [Perhaps we may also read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~apa Alv~uzay~aA Alqamara","text_ar":"عِدَّةَ الثُّزَيَّا القَمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mdaAd","text_ar":"مدَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ed","text_ar":"عد"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixolaAfu AlwaEodi mino A^axolaAqi Alwagodi","text_ar":"اـِخْلَافُ الوَعْدِ مِنْ اَخْلَاقِ الوَغْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The breaking of a promise is one of the natural habits of the mean and base"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. A saying of the Arabs. (MF.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEodN","text_ar":"وَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fulfilment of a promise."},{"kind":"text","text":"Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataY h`*aA AlwaEodu","text_ar":"مَتَى هٰذَا الوَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, [x. 49, &c.] means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When shall be the fulfilment of this promise?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b6-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing promised."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"njz","text_ar":"نجز"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","T","S","Msb","Fr"]}]}}